rors.\", \"from\": 1062, \"to\": 1145, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1095, \"end\": 1098, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Court_of_Arbitration_for_Sport\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.0539972229985673e-21, \"text\": \"CAS\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Court_of_Arbitration_for_Sport\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Court_of_Arbitration_for_Sport\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The USOPC\", \"from\": 1063, \"to\": 1072}, {\"ngram\": \"significant procedural errors\", \"from\": 1115, \"to\": 1144}]}, {\"sentence\": \"From August 6-9, CAS sent crucial communications to erroneous email addresses at USOPC and USAG, an error not corrected until Aug. 9 - three days after filing, two days past the deadline to submit objections and less than 24 hours before the hearing.\", \"from\": 1146, \"to\": 1396, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1163, \"end\": 1166, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Court_of_Arbitration_for_Sport\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.0539972229985673e-21, \"text\": \"CAS\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Court_of_Arbitration_for_Sport\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Court_of_Arbitration_for_Sport\"}, {\"begin\": 1237, \"end\": 1241, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Gymnastics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"USAG\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Gymnastics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Gymnastics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"August\", \"from\": 1151, \"to\": 1157}, {\"ngram\": \"crucial communications\", \"from\": 1172, \"to\": 1194}, {\"ngram\": \"erroneous email addresses\", \"from\": 1198, \"to\": 1223}, {\"ngram\": \"USOPC\", \"from\": 1227, \"to\": 1232}, {\"ngram\": \"an error\", \"from\": 1243, \"to\": 1251}, {\"ngram\": \"filing\", \"from\": 1298, \"to\": 1304}, {\"ngram\": \"the deadline\", \"from\": 1320, \"to\": 1332}, {\"ngram\": \"objections\", \"from\": 1343, \"to\": 1353}, {\"ngram\": \"the hearing\", \"from\": 1384, \"to\": 1395}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It continued, saying, the CAS' action deprived the US authorities of sufficient time to acquire relevant evidence or to respond constructively.The US body further claimed that new evidence supports their objection, including \\\"mishandlings by CAS and administrative errors by FIG (The International Gymnastics Federation)\\\", which they were unable to bring up at the time due to urgent hearing.Stating that they were not given a significant chance to be heard, they are dedicated to pursuing an appeal to guaranteeJordan Chilesgets the credit she deserves.\", \"from\": 1396, \"to\": 1951, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1423, \"end\": 1426, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Court_of_Arbitration_for_Sport\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.0539972229985673e-21, \"text\": \"CAS\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Court_of_Arbitration_for_Sport\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Court_of_Arbitration_for_Sport\"}, {\"begin\": 1448, \"end\": 1450, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_government_of_the_United_States\", \"score\": 0.8683727691497558, \"rank\": 0.1515764900221525, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_government_of_the_United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_government_of_the_United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 1639, \"end\": 1642, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Court_of_Arbitration_for_Sport\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.0539972229985673e-21, \"text\": \"CAS\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Court_of_Arbitration_for_Sport\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Court_of_Arbitration_for_Sport\"}, {\"begin\": 1672, \"end\": 1675, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Gymnastics_Federation\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.695572610008435e-29, \"text\": \"FIG\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q